The paper deals with the problem of data monetization and privacy, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper also proposes a contract-theoretic approach to address this problem, which is related to the fields of data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the effects of adversarial users on the data seller's revenue, which is a topic of interest in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
